# Slim BT config for HomePlate's OpenDisplay BLE transport.
#
# Goal: rebuild the framework's libbt.a so a BLE GATT server fits in
# classic ESP32's 128KB IRAM alongside WiFi + Inkplate driver. The stock
# pioarduino prebuilt overflows by ~4KB because it ships with Classic BT,
# A2DP, AVRCP, SPP, HFP, BLE Mesh, BLUFI all enabled.
#
# Strategy: keep the Bluedroid host (so pioarduino's hardcoded `-lbt`
# link line keeps working unchanged), but disable everything we don't
# need, and switch the BT controller from BTDM (BLE+Classic combined) to
# BLE-only — that controller change is the biggest single IRAM win.
#
# We do NOT switch to NimBLE here because pioarduino's pioarduino-build.py
# hardcodes Bluedroid-style library names; switching hosts would require
# patching that file too. Slimming Bluedroid gives us enough.

# --- Controller: BLE only -------------------------------------------------
# Drops BR/EDR controller code from libbtdm_app.a — biggest IRAM saving.
# CONFIG_BTDM_CTRL_MODE_BTDM is not set
# CONFIG_BTDM_CTRL_MODE_BR_EDR_ONLY is not set
CONFIG_BTDM_CTRL_MODE_BLE_ONLY=y

# --- Host: keep Bluedroid, drop everything we don't need ------------------
# CONFIG_BT_CLASSIC_ENABLED is not set
# CONFIG_BT_A2DP_ENABLE is not set
# CONFIG_BT_AVRCP_ENABLED is not set
# CONFIG_BT_SPP_ENABLED is not set
# CONFIG_BT_HFP_ENABLE is not set
# CONFIG_BT_HFP_CLIENT_ENABLE is not set
# CONFIG_BT_HFP_AG_ENABLE is not set
# CONFIG_BT_GOEPC_ENABLED is not set

# NOTE: GATTC stays enabled. We don't need it, but Arduino-ESP32's bundled
# BLE library's BLEClient.cpp hardcodes esp_ble_gattc_* calls and won't
# compile out, so disabling GATTC fails the firmware link. The IRAM saving
# from disabling it would be small (host-side only — controller is unaffected).

# Extras we don't use.
# CONFIG_BLE_MESH is not set
# CONFIG_BT_BLE_BLUFI_ENABLE is not set
# CONFIG_USE_BLE_ONLY_FOR_COMMISSIONING is not set
